-- Ukraine’s DTEK Acquires Bilozerska Coal Mine in Donetsk Region
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-03-06T13:13:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/ukraine-s-dtek-acquires-bilozerska-coal-mine-in-donetsk-region.html
DTEK, Ukraine’s biggest private
power producer, acquired TDV Shakhta Bilozerska, a  coal mine  in
Donetsk region, for an undisclosed sum.  DTEK, which is based in the city of Donetsk, said in an e-
mailed statement that it now owns 95.4 percent of the mine. The
company plans to invest in Bilozerska and increase output to
more than 1 million metric tons of coal next year and 1.35
million tons in 2014.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Moscow at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
